  "prompt": "Which US Senate seats are up for reelection in 2018?",
  "response": "In the 2018 United States Senate elections, **33 of the 100 seats** were up for reelection. These included:\n\n1. **Class 1 Senate seats** (elected in 2012, up for election again in 2018).\n2. **Special elections** were held for seats that became vacant during the 115th Congress.\n\nHere\u2019s a breakdown by state:\n\n### 1. **Class 1 Senate Seats (All 33 seats):**\n   - **Arizona:** Jeff Flake (R) \u2013 Retired (Winner: Kyrsten Sinema, D)\n   - **California:** Dianne Feinstein (D) \u2013 Reelected\n   - **Connecticut:** Chris Murphy (D) \u2013 Reelected\n   - **Delaware:** Tom Carper (D) \u2013 Reelected\n   - **Florida:** Bill Nelson (D) \u2013 Lost to Rick Scott (R)\n   - **Hawaii:** Mazie Hirono (D) \u2013 Reelected\n   - **Indiana:** Joe Donnelly (D) \u2013 Lost to Mike Braun (R)\n   - **Maine:** Angus King (I) \u2013 Reelected\n   - **Maryland:** Ben Cardin (D) \u2013 Reelected\n   - **Massachusetts:** Elizabeth Warren (D) \u2013 Reelected\n   - **Michigan:** Debbie Stabenow (D) \u2013 Reelected\n   - **Minnesota:** Amy Klobuchar (D) \u2013 Reelected\n   - **Mississippi:** Roger Wicker (R) \u2013 Reelected (Also won a special election for the remaining term)\n   - **Missouri:** Claire McCaskill (D) \u2013 Lost to Josh Hawley (R)\n   - **Montana:** Jon Tester (D) \u2013 Reelected\n   - **Nebraska:** Deb Fischer (R) \u2013 Reelected\n   - **Nevada:** Dean Heller (R) \u2013 Lost to Jacky Rosen (D)\n   - **New Jersey:** Bob Menendez (D) \u2013 Reelected\n   - **New Mexico:** Martin Heinrich (D) \u2013 Reelected\n   - **New York:** Kirsten Gillibrand (D) \u2013 Reelected\n   - **North Dakota:** Heidi Heitkamp (D) \u2013 Lost to Kevin Cramer (R)\n   - **Ohio:** Sherrod Brown (D) \u2013 Reelected\n   - **Pennsylvania:** Bob Casey Jr. (D) \u2013 Reelected\n   - **Rhode Island:** Sheldon Whitehouse (D) \u2013 Reelected\n   - **Tennessee:** Bob Corker (R) \u2013 Retired (Winner: Marsha Blackburn, R)\n   - **Texas:** Ted Cruz (R) \u2013 Reelected (Defeated Beto O\u2019Rourke, D)\n   - **Utah:** Orrin Hatch (R) \u2013 Retired (Winner: Mitt Romney, R)\n   - **Vermont:** Bernie Sanders (I) \u2013 Reelected\n   - **Virginia:** Tim Kaine (D) \u2013 Reelected\n   - **Washington:** Maria Cantwell (D) \u2013 Reelected\n   - **West Virginia:** Joe Manchin (D) \u2013 Reelected\n   - **Wisconsin:** Tammy Baldwin (D) \u2013 Reelected\n   - **Wyoming:** John Barrasso (R) \u2013 Reelected\n\n### 2. **Special Elections:**\n   - **Minnesota:** Seat held by Al Franken (D), who resigned in January 2018. Tina Smith (D) was appointed and then won the special election.\n   - **Mississippi:** Seat held by Thad Cochran (R), who resigned in April 2018. Cindy Hyde-Smith (R) was appointed and then won the special election.\n\nThe 2018 elections resulted in a net gain of **+2 seats for Republicans**, as they flipped seats in Indiana, Missouri, North Dakota, and Florida, while Democrats won seats in Arizona and Nevada.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
